{"type":"message","id":"521bda6a","parentId":"9bf3760c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:14:03.437Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the newest file in the session directory is `pulse_2026-03-24 001230.md`, not `pulse_2026-03-24 001328.md`. The 001230 file seems to be the one I should read. But the pulse log says it created `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 001328.md`. Let me check if there's a different path or maybe the file was created elsewhere.\n\nWait, looking at the output more carefully:\n- The command returned `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 001230.md`\n\n\n- But the pulse output shows it created `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 001328.md`\n\nThis could be a path resolution issue since the pulse runs in a different working directory. Let me just read the file that was actually returned by the command.","thinkingSignature":"414368bbdbe61e10d7c2be907bec11b1d742717170bc8f64f683db2374f0f96d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vczbjs6drmbc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 001230.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":713,"output":251,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12842,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774325637339}}
{"type":"message","id":"716fa296","parentId":"521bda6a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:14:03.446Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vczbjs6drmbc_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 001230\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a pending TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n3. Next action is to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is the \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure. The next step is to implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nSo my action should be to:\r\n- Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n- This should analyze the pulse logs and identify invariant vs variant patterns\r\n- Then use those invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me implement a TIC classifier. I'll create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads pulse logs from the logs directory\r\n2. Extracts content patterns\r\n3. Classifies invariant vs variant elements\r\n4. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nI should start by examining the pulse log structure, then implement the classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `temporal_invariance_classifier.py` - a Python script that reads pulse logs, extracts structural invariants, classifies invariant/variant elements, and tests next-pulse prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```python\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_sections(content):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract named sections from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current_section = \"header\"\r\n    current_content = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        match = re.match(r'^##\\s+(.+)$', line)\r\n        if match:\r\n            if current_content:\r\n                sections[current_section] = '\\n'.join(current_content).strip()\r\n            current_section = match.group(1).lower()\r\n            current_content = []\r\n        else:\r\n            current_content.append(line)\r\n    \r\n    if current_content:\r\n        sections[current_section] = '\\n'.join(current_content).strip()\r\n    \r\n    return sections\r\n\r\ndef extract_tokens(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple tokenizer for structural analysis.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    return [t for t in tokens if len(t) > 2]\r\n\r\ndef compute_ngram_invariants(pulse_tokens, n=3):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract n-grams as potential invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    ngrams = []\r\n    for i in range(len(pulse_tokens) - n + 1):\r\n        ngram = tuple(pulse_tokens[i:i+n])\r\n        ngrams.append(ngram)\r\n    return ngrams\r\n\r\ndef analyze_pulse_corpus():\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze all pulse logs for invariant patterns.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 5:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return None\r\n    \r\n    # Extract sections and tokens from all pulses\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        content = pf.read_text(encoding='utf-8')\r\n        sections = extract_pulse_sections(content)\r\n        tokens = extract_tokens(content)\r\n        pulses.append({\r\n            'file': pf.name,\r\n            'sections': sections,\r\n            'tokens': tokens,\r\n            'ngrams': compute_ngram_invariants(tokens)\r\n        })\r\n    \r\n    # Count section name occurrences (structural invariants)\r\n    section_counts = Counter()\r\n    for p in pulses:\r\n        for section_name in p['sections'].keys():\r\n            section_counts[section_name] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants: sections appearing in >80% of pulses\r\n    threshold = 0.8 * len(pulse_files)\r\n    structural_invariants = [s for s, c in section_counts.items() if c >= threshold]\r\n    \r\n    # Token frequency analysis\r\n    all_tokens = []\r\n    for p in pulses:\r\n        all_tokens.extend(p['tokens'])\r\n    token_freq = Counter(all_tokens)\r\n    \r\n    # High-frequency tokens as semantic invariants\r\n    total_pulses = len(pulse_files)\r\n    semantic_invariants = [t for t, c in token_freq.items() \r\n                          if c >= threshold and t not in ['the', 'and', 'for', 'are', 'but']]\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'pulse_count': len(pulse_files),\r\n        'structural_invariants': structural_invariants,\r\n        'semantic_invariants': semantic_invariants[:20],  # Top 20\r\n        'token_freq': token_freq.most_common(30)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant_variants(pulse_content, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content elements as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    structural_inv = invariants.get('structural_invariants', [])\r\n    semantic_inv = set(invariants.get('semantic_invariants', []))\r\n    \r\n    sections = extract_pulse_sections(pulse_content)\r\n    classification = {'invariant': [], 'variant': []}\r\n    \r\n    for section_name, section_content in sections.items():\r\n        if section_name in structural_inv:\r\n            classification['invariant'].append(section_name)\r\n        else:\r\n            classification['variant'].append(section_name)\r\n    \r\n    # Classify key\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:12:52\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774325643444}}
{"type":"message","id":"8315ef8b","parentId":"716fa296","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:14:19.816Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is the 001230 pulse log. The 001328 pulse just ran but the file appears to have been created. Let me read the actual newest file. Let me check if the file was created in the sandbox's working directory (since the pulse runs from the sandbox directory).\n\nActually wait - looking at the output of the `ls` command again, it returned `pulse_2026-03-24 001230.md` as the newest. But the pulse said it created `pulse_2026-03-24 001328.md`. The path might be different. The pulse log says it created `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 001328.md`. \n\nThe `ls` command might have been run before the file was created. I'm noticing the output format is unusual—the full path appeared on the same line as the command, which suggests there might be some confusion about what actually ran. The pulse output references `pulse_2026-03-24 001328.md`, but the file listing shows `pulse_2026-03-24 001230.md` instead.\n\nLooking at the pulse results more carefully, the sandbox likely created the file in a different location than the workspace session directory. The timestamp discrepancy is interesting—the 001230 file was created at 12:12 AM and the 001328 at 12:13 AM. I'm trying to reconcile the timestamps: if the system shows 12:13 AM on March 24th in ET, that converts to 04:13 UTC, so the 001328 timestamp would correspond to 00:13:28 ET rather than 04:13.\n\nThe 001230 pulse is what actually exists and ran before this current one. The just-completed pulse (001328) should have created a new file, but I need to verify where it was actually written. Looking at the pulse script output showing \"create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 001328.md\", that's relative to the git directory. Since the workspace is C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace, the file would be at C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 001328.md, but when I checked the session directory, only the 001230 file appeared. The sandbox might be operating in a different git repository than the workspace itself, which could explain the discrepancy in where the file was created versus where I'm looking for it.","thinkingSignature":"6407c71be8c43b6c0d37237d162d44742ea84e0a428fa99515671009a30db1e0"},{"type":"text","text":"The newest file found is 001230, but the pulse created 001328. Let me check both:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w1wbp6phlrhm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\session\" -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 3 FullName, LastWriteTime","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w1wbp6phlrhm_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\" -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 3 FullName, LastWriteTime","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2277,"output":706,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14861,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774325643446}}
