{"type":"message","id":"6c05cf2a","parentId":"d0d92f66","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:14:22.621Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_aev3h0d0hqt2_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 001328\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: temporal_invariance_classifier.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and what needs to be done.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n- Phase 1 is focused on COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n- Next action is implementing TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier\r\n- Need to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy on pulse logs\r\n- Need to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe immediate next step should be implementing the TIC experiment. Looking at the pending actions, the key one is:\r\n\r\n\"TIC Experiment\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\"\r\n\r\nSo I need to create a TIC classifier script. Let me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures accuracy\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take right now is to create the TIC classifier implementation. This is the next logical step toward the experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me write a script that will:\r\n1. Load the pulse logs\r\n2. Implement basic TIC logic (extract features, compare across pulses, identify invariants)\r\n3. Run classification and prediction experiments\r\n4. Output metrics\r\n\r\nI'll create `scripts/tic_classifier.py` as the implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next concrete step for Phase 1 advancement. I need to implement the classifier that will test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs, classify content as invariant/variant, and measure prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Reads pulse logs from logs/\r\n- Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n- Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Outputs metrics against success criteria (>70% class., >60% pred.)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nWINDOW_SIZE = 5  # Compare last N pulses for invariance\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(pulse_text: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract distinguishing features from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    features = set()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract headers (## style)\r\n    headers = re.findall(r'^#{1,3}\\s+(.+)$', pulse_text, re.MULTILINE)\r\n    features.update(f\"hdr:{h.lower().strip()}\" for h in headers)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    files = re.findall(r'`([^`]+\\.\\w+)`', pulse_text)\r\n    features.update(f\"file:{f}\" for f in files)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract code blocks (as invariant structure markers)\r\n    code_blocks = re.findall(r'^```\\w*\\n[\\s\\S]*?^```', pulse_text, re.MULTILINE)\r\n    features.add(f\"codeblocks:{len(code_blocks)}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action verbs (present tense markers)\r\n    actions = re.findall(r'(?:Create|Implement|Write|Build|Design|Add|Remove|Update|Fix|Test)\\s+\\w+', pulse_text)\r\n    features.update(f\"action:{a.lower()}\" for a in actions)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goal references\r\n    goals = re.findall(r'(?:Goal|Phase|Task|Step)[\\s:]+(\\d+|[\\w\\s]+)', pulse_text, re.IGNORECASE)\r\n    features.update(f\"goal:{g.lower().strip()}\" for g in goals)\r\n    \r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariance_score(features_a: set, features_b: set) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"Compute Jaccard similarity as invariance score.\"\"\"\r\n    if not features_a or not features_b:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    intersection = len(features_a & features_b)\r\n    union = len(features_a | features_b)\r\n    return intersection / union if union > 0 else 0.0\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(pulse_features: set, window_features: list) -> bool:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant (>70% avg similarity in window).\"\"\"\r\n    if not window_features:\r\n        return False\r\n    scores = [compute_invariance_score(pulse_features, wf) for wf in window_features]\r\n    return sum(scores) / len(scores) >= 0.7\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_features: set, candidate_pulses: list) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse by finding most similar to invariant features.\"\"\"\r\n    if not invariant_features or not candidate_pulses:\r\n        return \"\"\r\n    best_score = 0\r\n    best_pulse = \"\"\r\n    for pulse, features in candidate_pulses:\r\n        score = compute_invariance_score(invariant_features, features)\r\n        if score > best_score:\r\n            best_score = score\r\n            best_pulse = pulse\r\n    return best_pulse\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    print(\"TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\")\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    \r\n    # Load pulse logs\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), \r\n                         key=lambda p: p.stat().st_mtime,\r\n                         reverse=True)[:20]  # Last 20 pulses\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 10:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR:\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:13:53\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774325662618}}
